snippet: Defense lawyers for James (Whitey) Bulger did not contest that Mr. Bulger was a gangland criminal of the first order.
abstract: Trial of mobster James (Whitney) Bulger is set to go to the jury; Bulger faces a sweeping 32-count indictment as overlord of Boston's underworld in the 1970s and1980s, including charges that he participated in 19 murders, of which the defense has contested only two.
lead_paragraph: Defense lawyers for James (Whitey) Bulger did not contest that Mr. Bulger was a gangland criminal of the first order.

headline.main: Boston Trial of Crime Boss Is Set to Go to the Jury
headline.print_headline: Boston Trial Of Crime Boss Is Set to Go To the Jury
